Because from your angle, the immediate classification problem — is AI native, alien, rupture, continuity, machine, mind-like, etc. — may be less important than the transformation underway in how reality is rendered, preserved, and expressed.

In other words:
the labels may matter less than the drift.

That is a powerful instinct.
A lot of people get trapped in naming the thing while the actual change moves underneath them.

